ЁЯЪА #100DaysOfCode Challenge - Day 94: Demystifying Network Routing! ЁЯМР

94 days of code, 94 days of breaking barriers! Today, I dove deep into network routing conceptsтАФthe backbone of how data travels across the internet! ЁЯТб
ЁЯФН What I Learned:
тЬФ Routing Tables = Internet GPS ЁЯЧ║я╕П

    Routers use these tables to decide the best path for data packets (like choosing the fastest highway for your trip!).

    Missing route? Traffic gets dropped with an "ICMP Host Unreachable" error. Ouch!

тЬФ Default Gateway = The "Plan B" Route ЁЯдЭ

    When a router doesnтАЩt know where to send traffic, it uses the gateway of last resort (0.0.0.0/0)тАФlike a safety net for lost packets!

тЬФ DHCP Drama: APIPA & Duplicate IPs тЪая╕П

    No DHCP response? Your PC panics and assigns itself a 169.254.x.x (APIPA) addressтАФworks locally but no internet for you! ЁЯШЕ

    Duplicate IPs? Chaos ensues! Pro tip: Always ping an IP before assigning it statically.
ЁЯТб Why It Matters:
Understanding routing helps troubleshoot why your Netflix wonтАЩt load (ЁЯШЙ) and how enterprises manage global networks.

ЁЯЩП Shoutout:
To the tech communities & mentors who make complex topics like this easier to grasp! Onward to Day 95!

